Deji Adeyanju, a popular socio-political commentator based in Abuja, has predicted that the All Progressives Congress, APC, will win the 2023 presidential election. Adeyanju made this known in a tweet on his Twitter page on Monday. According to him, the ruling party will emerge winner because opposition political parties are not united and are only interested in negotiating with APC. “APC will win next year’s general election because the opposition are not united. “They are only interested in popularity contests to build on their future political plans and also to negotiate with the APC led government to divide votes,” he wrote. Meanwhile, Bola Tinubu Ahmed is the APC’s presidential candidate, while Atiku Abubakar is the presidential candidate of the Peoples Democratic Party, PDP.